I think the backslash may be coming from my precmd ... has something chan=
ged
that would reduce the number of backslashes required to quote a backslash=
?

Possibly relevant fragment; this is happening with TERM=3Dscreen:

if [[ "$TERM" =3D screen ]]
then
    # Set top to introduce titlebar change
    top=3D'=1B^'
    # Set back to end titlebar change
    back=3D'=1B\\\\'
    # Set aka so screen can find the prompt
    aka() { print -n '=1Bk=1B\\' }
    precmd() { title ; aka }
elif [[ "$TERM" =3D xterm* ]]
then
    # Set top to introduce titlebar change
    top=3D'=1B]0;'
    # Set back to end titlebar change
    back=3D'=07'
    precmd() { title }
else
    return
fi

title() { print -nP "%{$top%m.%l:%2c - %t$back%}" }

